{
  "text": "So, it would be of interest to study the effect of preheating of low shrinking resin composite on the dentin microtensile bond strength and the intrapulpal temperature changes. The null hypotheses were: [CITATION_1] There is no difference in intrapulpal temperature whether silorane-based resin composite is preheated or not. (2) Dentin microtensile bond strength would not differ if silorane-based resin composite was applied at room temperature or after preheating.",
  "citation_candidates": [
